            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The behavior of vim and neovim is not different. This is also because the default `shortmessg` in neovim contains `F`. You can make neovim work the same way as vim by doing the following.\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -u NORC --cmd 'set shortmess-=F laststatus=0' test.txt\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, you can make vim work the same way as neovim by doing the following.\r\n\r\n```\r\nvim -Nu NORC --cmd 'set shortmess+=F laststatus=2' test.txt\r\n```",
